# Welcome to the Neighborhood

<img src="https://images.code.org/b448b13c66c9f0104a8a62e50340df88-image-1741198407647.png" alt="neighborhood ide scene with taxi and donut truck" width="180px" style="border-radius:20px; float:right; margin: 0 20px 10px 0px;">



#### The Neighborhood IDE provides an engaging, visual approach to learning programming by allowing users to control a painter's character to navigate a neighborhood and create patterns.

#### This interactive environment supports foundational coding skills while reinforcing computational thinking in an intuitive, exploratory way.

#### It encourages creativity and problem-solving, making coding more enjoyable for learners of all levels.

<br>



## Why this approach works

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold;">👁️ Visual and Immediate Feedback </summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
<p style="font-size: 16px;"> Seeing the painter move and create patterns helps learners quickly connect code to outcomes, reinforcing cause-and-effect relationships in programming.
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold;">⚖️ Low Barrier to Entry</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
<p style="font-size: 16px;"> The simple text commands make it accessible for beginners, reducing cognitive load while building confidence.
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold;">🧠 Supports Computational Thinking</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
<p style="font-size: 16px;">Concepts like sequencing, loops, and conditionals are introduced naturally as students direct the painter’s movement and actions.
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold;">🎨 Creativity and Engagement </summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
<p style="font-size: 16px;"> Painting patterns and exploring the neighborhood make coding feel playful, promoting experimentation and problem-solving.
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold;">🌉 Bridges to More Complex Coding </summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
<p style="font-size: 16px;">  The structured yet flexible environment helps students transition from basic commands to more advanced programming concepts over time.
</p></div>
</details>

---

